### Propagation Narrative

1. **`ts-basic-service`** (ROOT CAUSE): CPU load surged to 298 (peak) on 128-core system; thread pool queue exploded from avg 9 → avg 38.75 (max 173), causing it to reject new connection attempts
2. **`ts-travel2-service`** → received connection-refused errors (no HTTP response, 1–8ms) when calling `POST /api/v1/basicservice/basic/travels`, causing 80%+ error rate on `trips/left` and 100% on `trip_detail`
3. **`ts-route-plan-service`** → calls `ts-travel2-service/trip_detail` which returns HTTP 500, causing 25% error rate on all routePlan endpoints
4. **`ts-travel-plan-service`** → calls `ts-route-plan-service` which returns HTTP 500, causing 30% error rate on all travelPlan endpoints (cheapest/quickest/minStation)
5. **`ts-ui-dashboard`** → receives HTTP 500 from both `ts-travel2-service` (direct) and `ts-travel-plan-service` (chained), resulting in SLO violations on all 4 reported endpoints
